BAFANA BAFANA and Bidvest Wits defender, Thulani Hlatshwayo, kicked off the new year with the goal of his life.This after the flamboyant player, who is also known as &ldquo;Tyson&rdquo;, secretly married his long-term girlfriend, Kenosi Masegela, last weekend in Soweto.Sources said other PSL players came in numbers to grace the occasion &ndash; including Mamelodi Sundowns&rsquo; Keagan Dolly, Kaizer Chiefs&rsquo; Sibusiso Khumalo and Ramahlwe Mphahlele, Orlando Pirates&rsquo; Happy Jele.An excited Tyson posted his wedding pictures on his Instagram page, and his fans were equally happy for him.A soccer star, who didn&rsquo;t want to be named, said: &ldquo;The wedding was supposed to take place last year in December, but due to a hectic festive schedule, he decided to postpone it to January. &ldquo;I&rsquo;m happy Tyson eventually walked down the aisle and is setting a good example for us as his teammates.&rdquo;Speaking to Sunday Sun, Tyson said: &ldquo;I&rsquo;m a private person, please call me 10 minutes after training. I&rsquo;ll give you the full story.&rdquo;But efforts to get hold of him and his wife to comment drew a blank.He also failed to respond to our SMSes.